title: The Romance of a Christmas Card
creator: Kate Douglas Wiggin
description: LibriVox recording of The Romance of a Christmas Card, by Kate Douglas Wiggin. Read by Allyson Hester. The story of the mission of two Christmas cards written by a minister’s wife. These cards find their way to two straying sheep from the village fold, who hear through the message in the words, and the little scenes on the cards, the compelling voice of home. There was inspiration and good cheer in the cards, and from them came, in one case reformation, in the other romance. (Summary compiled by Maria Therese from various original 1915 reviews) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: Librivox; audiobook; christmas; fiction
